07:58.521 --> 07:59.827
How you feeling?

07:59.827 --> 08:01.698
I'm fine, Daddy.

08:05.180 --> 08:07.791
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where you going?

08:07.791 --> 08:10.794
To the Hotel Theresa
to meet Malcolm.

08:10.794 --> 08:14.494
I'm gonna get some of my men
to drive you over there.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.539
To protect me...

08:16.539 --> 08:19.411
or to make sure I don't
go back to using duji?

08:19.411 --> 08:21.631
Maybe a little of both.

08:21.631 --> 08:24.416
Praise Allah. I have looked
the monster in the eye

08:24.416 --> 08:26.549
and I've killed him.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.246
You can trust me.

08:28.246 --> 08:30.553
It's my fault.

08:30.553 --> 08:33.513
I, uh, got mixed up
with the wrong people.

08:33.513 --> 08:36.428
You're always mixed up
with the wrong people.

08:36.428 --> 08:37.952
I've accepted that.

08:39.780 --> 08:41.825
Yeah.

08:41.825 --> 08:44.088
You going to the Audubon
this afternoon?

08:44.088 --> 08:46.003
Yes.
Of course.

08:46.003 --> 08:48.528
I got Chance and Pettigrew
working with Omar

08:48.528 --> 08:51.443
to lock down
that ballroom.

08:51.443 --> 08:54.708
I feel a little guilty we're
operating behind Malcolm's back.

08:54.708 --> 08:58.276
Yeah, well, his back needs
to be covered,

08:58.276 --> 08:59.930
as well as his front.

09:07.677 --> 09:08.983
I love you.

09:10.593 --> 09:12.203
You, too, Daddy.

09:29.612 --> 09:33.050
Big day today.

09:33.050 --> 09:37.228
My father actually agreed
to let you be in charge?

09:37.228 --> 09:39.970
He saw the wisdom of it,
from what I can tell.

09:41.493 --> 09:44.584
Told him Randall's Island
was your idea.

09:44.584 --> 09:48.892
I think he knows we have
feelings for each other.

09:48.892 --> 09:52.243
That don't sound
like my father.

09:52.243 --> 09:54.463
I can handle Chin.

09:54.463 --> 09:56.291
He'll get his piece
of the shipment,

09:56.291 --> 09:59.250
make a fortune,
all will be well.

10:00.904 --> 10:02.602
You okay?

10:06.301 --> 10:08.216
I think
we should stop it.

10:10.479 --> 10:13.308
What are you talking about?

10:13.308 --> 10:14.744
It.

10:14.744 --> 10:16.833
This. Us.

10:16.833 --> 10:19.444
It was a mistake.

10:19.444 --> 10:21.490
Why?
What's wrong?

10:21.490 --> 10:24.101
My father's lying.

10:24.101 --> 10:26.408
There's no way
he'll accept us together.

10:29.019 --> 10:30.891
I like you, Joe.

10:34.677 --> 10:37.549
I don't wanna see
you end up dead.

11:00.311 --> 11:01.704
China?

11:01.704 --> 11:05.055
Nobody cares about you
in China.

11:05.055 --> 11:07.362
We'll be safe there.

11:08.972 --> 11:11.671
Only my sister would think
to buy us tickets

11:11.671 --> 11:15.065
to a Communist country
for safety's sake.

11:15.065 --> 11:17.198
She's worried.

11:17.198 --> 11:18.852
And so am I.

11:18.852 --> 11:20.854
Aren't you?

11:20.854 --> 11:22.725
Between you and Ella,

11:22.725 --> 11:24.727
I think there's enough
worry to go around.

11:24.727 --> 11:27.077
What do you expect?

11:27.077 --> 11:29.645
Ella loves you
almost as much as I do.

11:33.954 --> 11:39.699
Betty Shabazz, ah, you are
my Crescent and Star.

11:42.397 --> 11:44.007
I'd like to bring
the older girls

11:44.007 --> 11:45.530
to the Audubon
this afternoon.

11:45.530 --> 11:48.446
Oh, no.
I'm not sure that's wise.

11:48.446 --> 11:52.842
We may find Afro-American unity
to be a fascinating subject,

11:52.842 --> 11:55.105
but they'll be
bored to tears.

11:55.105 --> 11:58.456
They watched their house
burn down to the ground.

11:58.456 --> 12:00.197
They should see how
their father carries on

12:00.197 --> 12:02.504
despite the forces
against him.

12:05.072 --> 12:08.597
After the speech, we'll pack
our things for the trip.

12:08.597 --> 12:10.730
Mm.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.601
Do you think
the food in China is, uh,

12:12.601 --> 12:14.472
anywhere near as good
as Wo Hop?

12:17.867 --> 12:19.913
Mm.

12:22.045 --> 12:23.917
Joe Bonanno
was banned from New York

12:23.917 --> 12:26.397
and Chin Gigante
was put behind bars.

12:26.397 --> 12:28.922
So, in my absence,

12:28.922 --> 12:34.101
Joe Colombo has taken over
the Five Families.

12:34.101 --> 12:37.191
But there's no active
investigation against him.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.455
Care to explain?

12:42.849 --> 12:47.114
Sir, the-- the DOJ directive
came in loud and clear.

12:47.114 --> 12:49.072
We're to focus
our prosecutorial efforts

12:49.072 --> 12:51.161
on Black militant leaders.

12:51.161 --> 12:52.902
Namely Malcolm X.

12:52.902 --> 12:55.122
He's calling for a violent
revolution in the streets.

12:55.122 --> 12:56.601
Maybe you need to go back
to law school

12:56.601 --> 12:58.081
and read
the First Amendment.

12:58.081 --> 13:00.127
It's called free speech.

13:00.127 --> 13:03.173
The Department of Justice
is rightly concerned

13:03.173 --> 13:07.090
about a charismatic leader
who'd unite all factions

13:07.090 --> 13:09.353
of the so-called
civil rights movement.

13:09.353 --> 13:11.703
Mr. Morgenthau,
there's someone here to see you.

13:11.703 --> 13:14.097
Um, I'm a little busy.

13:14.097 --> 13:16.012
It's Ellsworth Johnson.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.104
Alright, send him in.

13:21.104 --> 13:23.324
What the hell
do you think he wants?

13:23.324 --> 13:25.674
Hell if I know.

13:25.674 --> 13:26.849
Hey, fellas.

13:26.849 --> 13:28.329
Mr. Johnson.

13:28.329 --> 13:31.506
This is Assistant
District Attorney Pike.

13:31.506 --> 13:33.290
I'm aware of Mr. Pike.

13:33.290 --> 13:36.032
He likes to spend his time
harassing my wife to get to me.

13:37.729 --> 13:40.254
Well, here I am.

13:41.385 --> 13:43.039
And why are you here?

13:43.039 --> 13:45.563
I'm a concerned citizen
with an anonymous tip.

13:55.225 --> 13:56.661
<i>Congressman Powell
is here</i>

13:56.661 --> 13:58.141
<i>to see you, Mr. President.</i>

13:58.141 --> 13:59.839
Well, send him the hell in.

14:02.363 --> 14:05.235
In honor of
the 24th Amendment,

14:05.235 --> 14:09.587
I have brought us
some of the good stuff.

14:09.587 --> 14:12.329
Yeah, well, I don't feel
much like celebrating

14:12.329 --> 14:15.028
when my so-called
civil rights champion

14:15.028 --> 14:17.726
in Congress
stabs me in the back.

14:17.726 --> 14:19.771
Ah, don't worry
about the education bill.

14:19.771 --> 14:22.383
I will bring that
to the floor

14:22.383 --> 14:26.953
once you guarantee
an extra $400,000 for Harlem.

14:29.216 --> 14:31.522
There's no pleasing you,
is there?

14:31.522 --> 14:33.916
I just eliminated all poll tax
for Negroes.

14:33.916 --> 14:35.613
Which should never have been
there in the first place.

14:35.613 --> 14:40.575
I mean, can you imagine forcing
people to pay a fee to vote?

14:42.142 --> 14:44.361
In 1942, as a councilman,

14:44.361 --> 14:46.886
I walked from Union Station
to the Capitol

14:46.886 --> 14:48.713
to protest a poll tax
on Negroes,

14:48.713 --> 14:54.676
and it took until 1965
to be removed.

14:57.418 --> 14:59.811
Now, we both know
that our enemies

14:59.811 --> 15:03.467
will find other means
to suppress the vote.

15:03.467 --> 15:07.384
Everything I'm about is getting
that Voting Rights Act passed,

15:07.384 --> 15:10.953
but I need
an education bill first.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.737
Gotta help me.

15:12.737 --> 15:15.566
Take the pork out of your bill
and bring it to the floor.

15:15.566 --> 15:17.481
I'm begging you.
Come on now.

15:21.485 --> 15:22.747
Okay.

15:22.747 --> 15:24.532
Fine.

15:25.489 --> 15:31.060
Our democracy won't mean shit
without a Voting Rights Act.

15:31.060 --> 15:36.631
And a Voting Rights Act won't
mean shit unless people vote.

15:36.631 --> 15:38.546
Well, I'll drink to that.

15:41.375 --> 15:43.986
I confess to being, um,

15:43.986 --> 15:47.598
a little bit surprised,
Mr. Johnson.

15:47.598 --> 15:49.818
I thought
you didn't snitch.

15:49.818 --> 15:51.951
I don't.

15:51.951 --> 15:54.083
So what the fuck
is this?

15:54.083 --> 15:55.519
Why are you
wasting our time?

15:55.519 --> 15:57.347
Morgenthau's right.

15:57.347 --> 16:00.437
I don't snitch on partners
or colleagues

16:00.437 --> 16:04.137
unless they work for
the United States government.

16:05.051 --> 16:07.009
I'm listening.

16:07.009 --> 16:10.621
For the last three months,
the Central Intelligence Agency

16:10.621 --> 16:12.884
has been pipe-lining
seized cocaine

16:12.884 --> 16:15.278
to fund a second invasion
of Cuba.

16:15.278 --> 16:18.803
Now they're moving into heroin
and gun-running as well.

16:18.803 --> 16:23.199
The operation's run by a man
by the name of William Harvey.

16:23.199 --> 16:25.158
He started
as an FBI man.

16:25.158 --> 16:27.203
From what I'm told,
he was on your side

16:27.203 --> 16:29.162
until he jumped
to the CIA.

16:33.601 --> 16:35.690
Okay.

16:35.690 --> 16:37.692
We'll bite.

16:37.692 --> 16:39.520
What information you got
on Harvey?

16:43.611 --> 16:46.092
Morgenthau, you know
that's not the way it works.

16:47.702 --> 16:51.010
Before I spill,
we gotta make a deal.

16:56.493 --> 17:00.410
Entrances here,
two exits in the back,

17:00.410 --> 17:02.021
staircase here
from the lobby,

17:02.021 --> 17:04.762
bathrooms just outside
the entrance.

17:04.762 --> 17:07.069
The folding chairs
will be in rows.

17:07.069 --> 17:10.159
Better split up the chairs,
make a center aisle.

17:10.159 --> 17:11.856
Why's that?

17:11.856 --> 17:14.033
Somebody pulls out a piece,
we can get to 'em faster.

17:15.773 --> 17:17.427
Alright.

17:17.427 --> 17:19.603
Makes sense.

17:19.603 --> 17:21.910
Junie, I want you out front

17:21.910 --> 17:23.738
frisking anybody
who want to come in.

17:23.738 --> 17:25.696
- You got it.
- We can't do that.

17:25.696 --> 17:27.046
Why not?

17:27.046 --> 17:29.700
Malcolm doesn't want
anyone frisked.

17:29.700 --> 17:31.876
What in the hell
you talking about?

17:31.876 --> 17:35.184
Malcolm doesn't want young
people put off by checkpoints.

17:35.184 --> 17:37.534
We're expecting a lot of
college students.

17:43.627 --> 17:45.455
How in the hell are we supposed
to protect a motherfucker

17:45.455 --> 17:47.240
who don't want
protection?

17:49.111 --> 17:50.895
You know what?

17:50.895 --> 17:54.943
I am in the mood
for a Cuba Libre.

17:55.987 --> 17:57.337
Okay.

17:59.121 --> 18:01.602
We're gonna take back
your homeland, Jose.

18:07.042 --> 18:08.696
What's wrong,
pal-o-mine?

18:11.525 --> 18:14.223
I know Bumpy Johnson.

18:14.223 --> 18:17.096
He's up to something,
believe me.

18:20.055 --> 18:23.145
Yeah, you're probably right.
But what can he do?

18:23.145 --> 18:24.973
Do not underestimate him.

18:26.888 --> 18:29.020
Ugh.
That's too sweet.

